## 🧪 **Testing Scripts**

### **Test Migration Locally:**
```bash
#!/bin/bash
# test-migration.sh

echo "🧪 Testing migration..."

# Generate migration
docker-compose exec user-service alembic revision --autogenerate -m "test migration"

# Dry run
docker-compose exec user-service alembic upgrade head --sql

# Apply
docker-compose exec user-service alembic upgrade head

# Verify
docker-compose exec user-service alembic current

echo "✅ Migration test complete!"
```

### **Test in Kubernetes:**
```bash
#!/bin/bash
# test-k8s-migration.sh

echo "🧪 Testing Kubernetes migration..."

# Create test job
kubectl create job migration-test --from=cronjob/user-service-migration --dry-run=client -o yaml > test-job.yaml

# Run test
kubectl apply -f test-job.yaml

# Watch logs
kubectl logs job/migration-test -f

# Cleanup
kubectl delete -f test-job.yaml

echo "✅ Kubernetes migration test complete!"
```

